article.headline: Gardner-Webb 74, Western Carolina 73,OT
article.story: BOILING SPRINGS, N.C. (AP) -- Antonio Russell scored 30 points but missed a 12-foot shot with 2.3 seconds left in overtime as Gardner-Webb came from behind to defeat Western Carolina 74-73 on Saturday. The Bulldogs (2-6) trailed by 17 points, 43-26, at the break but rallied by hitting 7-of-11 3-pointers in the final 20 minutes. That included a 3-pointer by Chris Gash with 26.3 seconds left in regulation to tie it at 69-69. The Bulldogs took the lead for good on its first overtime possession when Samba Fall scored to make it 71-69. Gardner-Webb missed shots in the final seconds to give Western Carolina (4-3) its final chance at the win, but Grayson Flittner corralled Russell's final attempt.
